{
  "texts": [
    "It creates a notification system for data intermediation service providers and allows entities that collect data for general interest purposes to register as \"data altruism organizations.\"",
    "In terms of scope, the DGA focuses on enabling voluntary data flows.",
    "With the DSA, potential alignments include facilitating external researcher access to platform data: indeed, DSA Article 31 mandates data access for studying risks, while DGA Chapter 2 governs data sharing and re-use from public sector bodies.",
    "However, tensions could emerge around intermediary liability if DGA data sharing provisions expand platforms' accountability for user-generated content.",
    "And DGA recognition of data cooperatives and altruism efforts could create unclear overlaps with DSA compliance."
  ]
}